---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Get Started — Reliquery" description="Set up Reliquery in five minutes: install, sign in, connect your brand documents, and run your first analysis.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose-styles">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink">Get started with Reliquery</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink/60 mt-3">Five steps. Five minutes. Your first brand audit by the end.</p>

    <!-- Step 1: Install -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">1</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Install the extension</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Add Reliquery from the Chrome Web Store. It takes a few seconds and requires no special permissions at install time.
        </p>
        <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/reliquery/kgkpejegjlfcmghgkcebfekdnocgohbi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-lg bg-primary px-5 py-2.5 text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-90 transition">
          Add to Chrome — Free
        </a>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Tip:</strong> After installing, pin Reliquery to your toolbar. Click the puzzle piece icon in Chrome's toolbar, then click the pin next to Reliquery. This makes it one click to open the side panel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2: Sign in -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">2</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Sign in</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Click the Reliquery icon in your toolbar to open the side panel. You'll see a sign-in screen.
        </p>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-ink/80 list-decimal pl-5">
          <li>Enter your email address and click <strong>Send code</strong></li>
          <li>Check your inbox for a verification code from Reliquery</li>
          <li>Enter the code and click <strong>Verify</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/60">
          Reliquery uses passwordless sign-in. No password to remember — just a one-time code each time you sign in.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3: Brand Reliquary -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">3</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Create and connect your Brand Reliquary</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Your Brand Reliquary is the collection of documents that define your brand — voice guidelines, positioning statements, design principles, messaging frameworks, or anything else that captures how your brand should show up. Most teams don't have these in one place yet. That's normal — and it's the whole point.
        </p>

        <!-- Starter template CTA — primary path for most users -->
        <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary bg-primary/5 p-6">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Start from our template</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
            We've built a starter Brand Reliquary with the files most teams need — voice and tone, positioning, visual identity, and approved terminology. Fork the repo, fill in the blanks with your brand's specifics, and connect it to Reliquery. Takes about 20 minutes.
          </p>
          <a href="https://github.com/SkolKraken/brand-reliquary-starter" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-lg bg-primary px-5 py-2.5 text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-90 transition">
            Fork the starter template on GitHub
          </a>
          <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl bg-white border border-black/10 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink">What's in the template:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li><code>voice-and-tone.md</code> — How your brand sounds (formal vs casual, humor, vocabulary)</li>
              <li><code>positioning.md</code> — What you do, who it's for, and why it matters</li>
              <li><code>visual-identity.md</code> — Colors, typography, imagery guidelines</li>
              <li><code>terminology.md</code> — Approved terms, forbidden words, and common mistakes</li>
              <li><code>mission-and-values.md</code> — The promises your brand actually makes</li>
              <li><code>boilerplate.md</code> — Taglines, one-liners, and elevator pitches</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/60">
              Markdown (<code>.md</code>) files work best. You don't need every file — even a single voice guide will dramatically improve your audits. Start small and add more as you go.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Connect instructions -->
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">Connect it to Reliquery</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
          Once your Brand Reliquary exists (forked template or your own repo), open the <strong>Settings</strong> dropdown in the side panel and find the <strong>Connect your Brand Reliquary</strong> card.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">GitHub repository</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              Paste your repository URL and click <strong>Connect</strong>. You can optionally specify a branch and subfolder path. Private repos require a GitHub personal access token with <code>repo</code> (read-only) scope.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Local folder</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              Prefer to keep files on your machine? Click <strong>Choose folder</strong> and select the folder containing your brand documents. Documents are read at analysis time and never uploaded.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 4: Home Base -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">4</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Set your Home Base</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Your Home Base is your website's URL. Reliquery uses it to know which pages are yours and which belong to competitors.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          In the <strong>Settings</strong> dropdown, find the <strong>Home Base</strong> card and enter your website URL (e.g. <code>https://yoursite.com</code>).
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> When you're on your own site and click Analyze, Reliquery runs <strong>Audit</strong> mode (brand alignment). When you're on a competitor's site, it runs <strong>Scout</strong> mode (competitive analysis). Home Base is what tells Reliquery which is which.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 5: First analysis -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">5</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Run your first audit</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Navigate to a page on your website in Chrome. Open the Reliquery side panel, make sure you're on the <strong>Audit</strong> tab, and click <strong>Analyze This Page</strong>.
        </p>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-ink/80 list-decimal pl-5">
          <li>Chrome may ask you to grant Reliquery access to the site — click <strong>Allow</strong></li>
          <li>Reliquery extracts the page content and sends it (along with your brand documents) for analysis</li>
          <li>In about 15–30 seconds, you'll see a brand alignment score, drift findings with citations, and suggested rewrites</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="mt-4 text-ink/80">
          That's it — you're set up. Every finding links back to the specific passage in your Brand Reliquary that it violates, so you always know <em>why</em> something was flagged.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What's next -->
    <div class="mt-16 rounded-2xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink">What's next</h2>
      <div class="mt-5 grid gap-4">
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-xl">&#x2694;&#xFE0F;</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Try Scout mode</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/70">Navigate to a competitor's website and click <strong>Analyze This Page</strong> from the Scout tab. You'll get a side-by-side competitive breakdown — category claim, voice, pricing — compared against your own positioning.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-xl">&#x2692;&#xFE0F;</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Try Forge mode</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/70">Switch to the Forge tab, enter your <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary underline">Anthropic API key</a>, and type a design instruction in plain English. Reliquery applies the CSS and HTML changes live to the page. Forge requires a Pro subscription.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-xl">&#x1F4E4;</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Export a battle card</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/70">After a Scout analysis, use the export button to generate a battle card you can share with your team — a one-page competitive snapshot grounded in your own brand positioning.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Help -->
    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <p class="text-ink/60 text-sm">
        Stuck? Email <a href="mailto:support@reliquery.app" class="text-primary underline">support@reliquery.app</a>
        or check the <a href="/support" class="text-primary underline">support page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
